headline: ClearBridge Dividend Strategy Portfolios Q1 2025 Commentary
summary: The S&P 500 Index declined 4.3% in the first quarter due to two distinct factors. Strategy outperformance (gross and net of fees) stemmed from several factors.

headline: Listen: Defense Contractors Thrive in Uncertain World, but Aren’t Immune to Tariffs
summary: This is an interesting time to be a U.S. defense contractor.  Every U.S. manufacturer faces increased costs because of import tariffs and other countries’ countermeasures, but those making weapons have reason to be both worried and hopeful.  As the Trump administration casts doubt on foreign defense commitments at the same time that it has pledged to spend more on the U.S. military, global armaments spending is on the rise—particularly in the European Union.
